comments.en: An ontology that describes a high school gymnasium in terms of its components, features, systems, possible uses and environmental aspects.

comment.en: High school dancing event such as prom, homecoming and others.
Artificial light sources need to be placed around the gym for adequate lighting and for night time use.
All components of the gymnasium should be easily accessible
A high school gym could provide service to the community during certain events.
A high school gymnasium can have use for the community that are not related to emergency. For instance voting venue during elections.
Windows carefully placed around the gym walls and may be skylight on the roof can provide natural light to the gym and conserve energy

comment.undefined: Events that are going to be hosted in the gymnasium

comment.en: Almost all activities to be carried out in the gymnasium require adequate lighting.
The right acoustic configuration need to be worked out during the design phase
A high school gymnasium can have use for the community during emergency situations. For instance providing shelter in the event of disaster.
Venue for school ceremonies such as commencement ceremonies
